@startuml workflow-sequence
title Millwright-Overseer Workflow — Sequence (simplified, mo commands only)

skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam maxMessageSize 280
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFF8DC
skinparam noteBorderColor #8B7500
skinparam participantBackgroundColor #F8F8F8
skinparam databaseBackgroundColor #EEF7FF

actor Overseer
participant Millwright
participant "Sub-agent\n(opt-in)" as SubAgent
participant "Brainstorming\nChain (isolated)" as Chain
database "Workflow Data\nmillwright-overseer/, docs/" as FS
database "Git" as Git

note over Millwright, FS
  **Reading:** Each "Millwright" arrow folds in helpers (progress.sh, todo.sh,
  blueprints.sh, review.sh, commits.sh, frontmatter.sh, validate-on-write hook).

  **Auto vs typed:** Overseer types /mo-run + /mo-continue (×2 / ×3). Millwright
  auto-fires /mo-apply-impact, /mo-plan-implementation, /mo-review,
  /mo-generate-implementation-diagrams, /mo-complete-workflow. Recovery:
  /mo-abort-workflow, /mo-resume-workflow, /mo-update-blueprint, /mo-update-todo-list.

  **Isolation:** stage-3 chain and stage-6 review session run isolated.
  /mo-continue is the explicit resumption signal.

  **Layered context (Rule 3):** primer.md and review-context.md are required first
  reads; canonical files (requirements / config / summary / todo-list) are on-demand.

  **Cache-keyed reuse:** implementation/change-summary.md is shared between
  /mo-update-blueprint and /mo-generate-implementation-diagrams via
  `commits.sh change-summary-fresh` (key = base-commit + head).

  **Sub-agent delegation (opt-in):** Stage 1 large intake, Stage 1.5 multi-feature
  ordering, Stage 4 change-summary body, Stage 6 finding clusters. Sub-agents write
  artifacts; reply is ≤20 lines; no central state mutations.
end note

== Stage 0 — Journal populated ==

group Stage 0 — Journal populated (overseer intake)
  Overseer -> FS : populate journal/<folder>/ with .md/.txt files
  Overseer -> Overseer : signal intake done\n(no mo command — /mo-run starts the workflow)
end

== Stage 1 — Quest scaffolded ==

group Stage 1 — Quest scaffolded (/mo-run)
  Overseer -> Millwright : /mo-run <folder1> [<folder2> ...]

  group Preflight (first invocation)
    Millwright -> FS : check CLIs / Python modules / MCP / skills
    alt deps missing
      Millwright --> Overseer : "Approve installs?"
      Overseer -> Millwright : y
      Millwright -> Millwright : install deps; continue same /mo-run
    else all ok
    end
  end

  Millwright -> FS : enumerate journal/<folders>/**/*.{md,txt}
  Millwright -> Millwright : Step 2.5 — size manifest\n(warn if any > 100KB or total > 500KB)

  alt large intake (over thresholds)
    Millwright --> Overseer : "Proceed with per-file summarization?"
    Overseer -> Millwright : proceed
    note over Millwright, SubAgent #LightCyan
      **Delegation:** one sub-agent per oversized file.
      Tier: general reasoning, medium effort.
    end note
    par per-file summarization
      Millwright -> SubAgent : delegate: read <file>, write digest
      SubAgent -> FS : read journal/.../<file>
      SubAgent -> FS : write scratch digest
      SubAgent --> Millwright : ≤20-line summary + path
    end
  else all files within thresholds
    Millwright -> FS : read journal directly
  end

  Millwright -> FS : quest.sh start <slug> <folders...>\n(creates quest/<slug>/, updates quest/active.md → status=active)
  Millwright -> FS : write quest/<slug>/todo-list.md\n(features grouped; `[ ] TODO — ID: ...`)
  Millwright -> FS : write quest/<slug>/summary.md\n(feature-indexed: ## Cross-cutting, ## Out-of-scope,\n## Feature: <name> ×N, ## Sources)
  Millwright -> FS : write quest/<slug>/progress.md (queue + active=null)
  Millwright --> Overseer : "Quest ready at quest/<slug>/. Mark items with `[x] (assignee)`."
end

== Stage 1.5 — Selection + queue confirm ==

group Stage 1.5 — Selection + queue confirm
  Overseer -> FS : edit quest/<active-slug>/todo-list.md\n([ ] TODO → [x] (emin) TODO for selected)
  Overseer -> Millwright : "Done. Prioritize."
  Millwright -> FS : promote [x] (name) TODO → PENDING\n(refuses [x] TODO without assignee)

  alt ≥3 features need ordering
    note over Millwright, SubAgent #LightCyan
      **Delegation:** codebase reference inspection.
      Tier: general reasoning, medium effort.
    end note
    Millwright -> SubAgent : delegate: inspect codebase deps
    SubAgent -> FS : grep / read candidate modules
    SubAgent --> Millwright : ≤20-line summary (order + edges)
  else 1–2 features
    Millwright -> FS : analyze deps inline
  end

  Millwright --> Overseer : "Proposed queue: <list>. Confirm?"
  Overseer -> Millwright : confirm
  Millwright -> FS : write quest/<active-slug>/queue-rationale.md\n(features, ## Order, ## Dependencies)
  Millwright -> FS : progress.sh reorder ...
end

== Stage 2 — Blueprints generated ==

group Stage 2 — Blueprints (/mo-apply-impact, auto-fired)
  Millwright -> Millwright : /mo-apply-impact
  Millwright -> FS : activate queue[0] into progress.md.active
  Millwright -> FS : read summary.md (## Cross-cutting + ## Feature: <active> + ## Out-of-scope)
  Millwright -> FS : write blueprints/current/requirements.md\n(## Goals + ## Planned + ## Non-goals)
  Millwright -> FS : write blueprints/current/config.md\n(≤10 entries / ≤2 lines; ## Skills + ## Rules + ## Load on demand;\n## GIT BRANCH pre-fill; ## Overseer Additions section)
  Millwright -> FS : render blueprints/current/diagrams/
  Millwright --> Overseer : "Blueprints ready. Reply `approve`."
  Overseer -> Millwright : approve
end

== Stage 3 — Chain launched ==

group Stage 3 — Chain (/mo-plan-implementation, auto-fired)
  Millwright -> Millwright : /mo-plan-implementation
  Millwright -> FS : validate ## GIT BRANCH (rejects main/master; HEAD must match)
  Millwright -> FS : promote PENDING → IMPLEMENTING (active feature)
  Millwright -> Git : rev-parse HEAD → base-commit
  Millwright -> FS : progress.md: branch, base-commit, sub-flow=chain-in-progress
  Millwright -> FS : Step 3.5 — write blueprints/current/primer.md\n(active scope, Goals excerpt, journal context, likely skills/rules)

  note over Millwright, Chain #LightYellow
    **Brainstorming primer (layered load):**
    - First read: blueprints/current/primer.md
    - On-demand: requirements.md, config.md,
      summary.md (active feature section), todo-list.md
  end note

  Millwright -> Chain : Skill(brainstorming) — primer + hand off

  note over Chain
    Isolated. brainstorming → writing-plans → executing-plans /
    subagent-driven-development → finishing-a-development-branch.
  end note

  Chain <-> Overseer : Q&A loop
  Chain -> FS : writes spec / plan under docs/superpowers/
  Chain -> Git : commits implementation
  Chain --> Overseer : "Branch complete." (chain exits)
end

== Stage 4 — Chain resumed ==

group Stage 4 — Chain resumed (/mo-continue, 1st)
  Overseer -> Millwright : /mo-continue
  Millwright -> FS : sub-flow=resuming
  Millwright -> Git : log base-commit..HEAD
  Millwright -> FS : implementation-completed=true
  Millwright --> Overseer : "Pick execution mode."
  Overseer -> Millwright : <choice>
  Millwright -> FS : execution-mode=<choice>; advance 3 → 4

  Millwright --> Overseer : "Drift check: reason or `continue`?"
  alt overseer supplied a reason
    Overseer -> Millwright : "<reason>"
    Millwright -> Millwright : /mo-update-blueprint <reason>
    note right of Millwright #LightCyan
      Rotate current/ → history/v[N+1]/ (incl. primer.md).
      Ensure change-summary.md is fresh (cache check).
      Regenerate Goals + diagrams + primer.md from
      change-summary.md + targeted hunks.
      Preserve ## GIT BRANCH + ## Overseer Additions.
      review.sh sync-refs re-points overseer-review.md /
      review-context.md / change-summary.md.
    end note

    alt many-area diff (regen needed)
      note over Millwright, SubAgent #LightCyan
        **Delegation:** write change-summary.md body.
        Tier: strong code-analysis, high effort.
        Bounded: hunks first, ≤3 callers/callees, skip generated.
      end note
      Millwright -> SubAgent : delegate: change-summary body
      SubAgent -> Git : git diff base..HEAD (bounded)
      SubAgent -> FS : write implementation/change-summary.md
      SubAgent --> Millwright : ≤20-line summary
    else cache fresh / small diff
      Millwright -> FS : reuse / inline-write change-summary.md
    end
  else "continue"
  end

  Millwright -> Millwright : /mo-generate-implementation-diagrams
  note right of Millwright
    change-summary-fresh → reuse cache (0) or regen (1/2).
    Frame diagrams from change-summary.md + targeted re-reads.
    Render base..HEAD with existing-vs-new convention.
  end note

  alt cache miss + many-area diff
    note over Millwright, SubAgent #LightCyan
      **Delegation:** write change-summary.md body
      (same recipe as /mo-update-blueprint Step 4a).
      Tier: strong code-analysis, high effort.
    end note
    Millwright -> SubAgent : delegate: change-summary body
    SubAgent -> Git : git diff base..HEAD (bounded)
    SubAgent -> FS : write implementation/change-summary.md
    SubAgent --> Millwright : ≤20-line summary
  else cache hit / small diff
    Millwright -> FS : reuse / inline-write change-summary.md
  end

  Millwright -> FS : create overseer-review.md skeleton
  Millwright -> FS : advance 4 → 5
  Millwright --> Overseer : "Stage 5 — review. Write findings or leave empty, then /mo-continue."
end

== Stage 5 — Overseer review ==

group Stage 5 — Overseer review
  Overseer -> FS : review code (base..HEAD) + diagrams/
  Overseer -> FS : edit overseer-review.md (### IR-NNN blocks, or empty)
  Overseer -> Millwright : /mo-continue (2nd)
end

== Stage 6 — Overseer review session (isolated) ==

group Stages 5→6 (/mo-continue, 2nd)
  Millwright -> FS : check open findings

  alt no findings
    Millwright -> FS : overseer-review-completed=true; advance 5 → 6 → 7
    Millwright --> Overseer : "Approved. Auto-finalizing."
  else findings
    Millwright -> Millwright : /mo-review
    Millwright -> FS : Step 2.5 — write implementation/review-context.md\n(reads change-summary.md if fresh, else commits.sh changed-files)

    alt >5 open findings
      note over Millwright, SubAgent #LightCyan
        **Delegation:** finding-cluster analysis.
        Tier: general reasoning (fix/re-implement) →
        most capable (re-plan/re-spec). Disjoint scopes;
        each writes findings/<cluster>.md.
      end note
      par per-cluster analysis
        Millwright -> SubAgent : delegate: cluster N (disjoint scope)
        SubAgent -> FS : inspect relevant code
        SubAgent -> FS : write findings/<cluster>.md
        SubAgent --> Millwright : ≤20-line cluster summary
      end
    else ≤5 findings
      Millwright -> Millwright : (no delegation)
    end

    note over Millwright, Chain #LightYellow
      **Review primer (layered load):**
      - First reads: review-context.md + overseer-review.md
      - On-demand: requirements.md, config.md, primer.md,
        summary.md (active feature section)
    end note

    Millwright -> Chain : Skill(brainstorming) — review primer
    Millwright --> Overseer : "Review session live. Drive to completion, then /mo-continue."

    note over Chain
      Isolated. Chain decides per-finding:
      fix / re-implement / re-plan / re-spec.
      No iteration cap. Overseer ends with `approve`.
    end note

    loop until `approve`
      Chain -> FS : address open findings
      Chain -> Git : new commits
      Chain -> FS : mark fixed in overseer-review.md
      Chain --> Overseer : "Findings addressed. `approve` or `go again`?"
      alt go again
        Overseer -> FS : edit overseer-review.md (new IR-NNN)
        Overseer -> Chain : "go again"
      else approve
        Overseer -> Chain : "approve"
      end
    end

    Chain --> Overseer : "Approved. Type /mo-continue."
  end
end

== Stage 6 → 7 — Post-review-session resume (/mo-continue, 3rd) ==

group Post-review-session resume
  Overseer -> Millwright : /mo-continue
  Millwright -> FS : sanity-check no open findings remain
  Millwright -> FS : sub-flow=none; overseer-review-completed=true; advance 6 → 7
  Millwright --> Overseer : "Approved. Auto-finalizing."
end

== Stage 8 — Completion ==

group Stage 8 — Completion (/mo-complete-workflow, auto-fired)
  Millwright -> Millwright : /mo-complete-workflow
  Millwright -> FS : promote IMPLEMENTING → IMPLEMENTED (active feature)
  Millwright -> Git : log base..HEAD → commits[]
  Millwright -> FS : populate `commits:` in requirements.md
  Millwright -> FS : rotate blueprints/current/ → history/v[N+1]/\n(incl. primer.md; writes reason.md kind=completion)
  Millwright -> FS : clear implementation/\n(overseer-review.md, review-context.md, change-summary.md, diagrams/)
  Millwright -> FS : archive feature → completed[]; active=null

  alt queue non-empty
    Millwright --> Overseer : "Next: <next>. Auto-proceeding."
    Millwright -> Millwright : /mo-apply-impact → loop to Stage 2
  else queue empty
    Millwright --> Overseer : "All complete. Run /mo-run for new cycle."
  end
end

== Out-of-band commands (recovery / manual) ==

note over Overseer, FS #LightGray
  **/mo-resume-workflow** — diagnostic dispatcher; no state mutation.

  **/mo-abort-workflow [--drop-feature={completed|requeue}]** — safe cancel.
  Reverts IMPLEMENTING → PENDING; clears implementation/ (overseer-review.md,
  review-context.md, change-summary.md, diagrams/); resets runtime fields.
  Preserves blueprints/current/ (incl. primer.md). Never touches git.

  **/mo-update-blueprint <reason>** — manual mid-cycle blueprint refresh.
  Same as Stage 4 auto-trigger. Stage 3+ only.

  **/mo-update-todo-list <add|cancel|set-state> ...** — manual todo edits.
  Never mutates blueprints or progress.md.
end note

@enduml
